title: Anti-racism protest erupts in Melbourne | Daily Mail Online
text: Woman almost RUN OVER as hundreds of anti-racism protesters clash with people heading to a fundraising dinner for the far-right group Q Society in Melbourne More than 100 protesters surrounded a bus bound for far-right group's fundraising dinner Guest speakers at the dinner include George Christensen and Cory Bernardi A driver was caught on camera trying to run down a protester It comes a day after cartoonist Larry Pickering said he can't stand Muslims and starts 'shaking' if he sees them in the street Ross Cameron also told the same event the New South Wales division of the Liberal Party 'is basically a gay club' Published: 08:02 GMT, 10 February 2017 | Updated: 09:43 GMT, 10 February 2017 9 shares
